<p><strong>National Institute for Health Research (NIHR): </strong></p>
<p>The NIHR: improving the health and wealth of the nation through research.</p>
<p>Established by the Department of Health, the NIHR:</p>
<ul>
<li>funds high quality research to improve health</li>
<li>trains and supports health researchers</li>
<li>provides world-class research facilities</li>
<li>works with the life sciences industry and charities to benefit all</li>
<li>involves patients and the public at every step</li>
<li>For further information, visit the <a href="https://www.nihr.ac.uk/" title="National Institute for Health and Care Research">National Institute for Health and Care Research website</a></li>
</ul>
<p>This call for research was commissioned by the National Institute of Health Research using Official Development Assistance (ODA) funding. The views expressed in this publication are those of the author(s) and not necessarily those of the NHS, the National Institute for Health Research or the Department of Health.</p>
<p><strong>Queen Margaret University’s Institute for Global Health and Development (IGHD) </strong></p>
<p>The Institute for Global Health and Development is a multidisciplinary centre for postgraduate education and research addressing contemporary health and development challenges in low and middle-income countries and their connection to global systems and trends.</p>
